<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-18T04:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-18T04:35:00-05:00" n="377" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War
                                1939/14116</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-18T13:00:00+03:25">August 18, 1941—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>95. The British and Russian notes, referred to in the Legation’s No.
                                    92,<note n="78" xml:id="d377fn78">Dated August 15, 8 a.m., <ref target="#pg_397">p. 397</ref>.</note> were delivered
                                Saturday. Other than a fresh surge of rumors and increasing
                                nervousness among foreigners there are no important developments to
                                report. There is no indication yet as to any new Iranian Government
                                order. The British Minister’s impression is that the Iranians are
                                still seeking a magic formula which will satisfy parties.
                                Developments are expected soon.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>